  "response": "A heart attack can cause significant chest pain and discomfort, but not all heart attacks are fatal. Many people survive with prompt medical treatment. Pain levels vary depending on the individual, but typical symptoms include:\n\n1. Chest pressure or squeezing sensation\n2. Pain radiating to arm, neck, or jaw\n3. Shortness of breath\n4. Cold sweats\n5. Nausea or lightheadedness\n\nProfessional medical help is crucial during a heart attack. If you or someone else experiences these symptoms, call emergency services immediately.",
